<paragraph blockId="65.[151,430,836,862]" box="[151,430,836,862]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,430,836,862]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,430,836,862]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[207,252,836,862]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Brachygluta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seri">seri</taxonomicName>
species-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1436,906,1003]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
This group contains the single species, 
<taxonomicName box="[592,665,908,931]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Brachygluta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seri">
<emphasis box="[592,665,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">B. seri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from a desert island in the Gulf of California. It is unique in having tergites 
<number box="[244,285,943,967]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
not obviously modified, and tergite 
<number box="[716,730,943,967]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
is nearly as long as tergite 
<number box="[1062,1077,943,967]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
. Tergite 
<number box="[1183,1197,943,967]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
has the disc basally impressed in the area where the indistinct discal carinae are present.
</paragraph>
